{
  "texts": [
    "A Hitchin representation is a homomorphism ρ ∈ Hom(π 1 (B), G), where G is the adjoint form of a split semi-simple Lie group, that can be continuously deformed to ι • ρ Fuch, where ρ Fuch: π 1 (B) → PSL 2 (R) is the holonomy of a hyperboilic structure on B 2 and ι: PSL 2 (R) → G is an irreducible representation.",
    "Note that Hitchin representations are automatically irreducible [Lab08, Prop.",
    "4.1.5], and the set of all Hitchin representations forms a union of connected components in the character variety Hom red (π 1 (B), G)/G, so-called Hitchin components.Proof of Theorem B.",
    "Let ρ ∈ Hom(π 1 (B), SL n (R)) be a representation such that, for ρ = Ad •ρ, the class [ρ] ∈ Hom red (π 1 (B), PSL n (R))/ PSL n (R) is in the Hitchin component.",
    "By [Lab08, Corollary 1.0.4], there is a conformal structure c on B 2 and a ρ-equivariant map h: ( B, c) → (PSL n (R)/PSO(n), g sym) that is harmonic and weakly conformal."
  ]
}